@DATABASE Clipboard V1.00
$VER: PureBasic - Clipboard library V1.00 (01.09.1999) © Fantaisie Software
@NODE MAIN "Clipboard V1.00"

  @{b}PureBasic - Clipboard V1.00@{ub}

    The 'ClipBoard' is a system which allows the sharing of information
    between applications. For example, you can put a piece of text in
    the clipboard and any program which uses text (text editor, word
    processor, database, etc.) can access your text in a transparent
    way. This works for any kind of data (sound, pictures, etc.).

  @{b}Commands summary:@{ub}

    @{" GetClipboardText  " LINK GetClipboardText}
    @{" SetClipboardText  " LINK SetClipboardText}

  @{b}Example:@{ub}

    @{" Text clipboard    " LINK "PureBasic:Examples/Sources/Clipboard.pb/Main"}

@ENDNODE


@NODE GetClipboardText

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  text$ = GetClipboardText()

    @{b}FUNCTION@{ub}
  Returns the current text which is in the Amiga clipboard,
  or if no text is found in the clipboard it returns a null
  string.

@ENDNODE


@NODE SetClipboardText

    @{b}SYNTAX@{ub}
  SetClipboardText(Text$)

    @{b}STATEMENT@{ub}
  Changes the Amiga clipboard's content with the text given in the
  parameter. You can pass a null text, but it won't change the Amiga
  clipboard.

@ENDNODE
